<span id="Description"></span>
==Descrição==

The '''Draft Scale Widget''' can be used to specify the Draft annotation scale. This scale determines the  {{PropertyView|Scale Multiplier}} of new [[Draft_Text|Draft Texts]], [[Draft_Dimension|Draft Dimensions]] and [[Draft_Label|Draft Labels]]. The widget is only available in the [[Image:Workbench_Draft.svg|24px]] [[Draft_Workbench|Draft Workbench]]. It is an [[#Preferences|optional]] GUI element that is located in the [[Status_Bar|Status Bar]].

[[Image:Draft_annotation_scale_widget_button.png]]
{{Caption|The Draft Scale Widget}}

<span id="Usage"></span>
==Utilização==

# Press the {{Button|x:x}} button in the [[Status_Bar|Status Bar]]. The button displays the current annotation scale.
# The scale menu opens.
# Do one of the following:
#* Select one of the standard scales.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Custom}} option:
#** In the dialog box that opens enter a custom scale using the {{Value|x:x}} or the {{Value|x<nowiki>=</nowiki>x}} format.
#** Press {{KEY|Enter}} or the {{Button|OK}} button.

[[Image:Draft_annotation_scale_widget_menu.png]]
{{Caption|The menu of the widget}}

<span id="Preferences"></span>
==Preferências==

See also: [[Preferences_Editor|Preferences Editor]] and [[Draft_Preferences|Draft Preferences]].

* The Draft Scale Widget is optional: {{MenuCommand|Edit → Preferences → Draft → Interface → Show the Draft Scale Widget in the Draft Workbench}}.
* To change the annotation scale without the widget: change the {{MenuCommand|Scale multiplier}} on the {{MenuCommand|Annotation}} tab of the [[Draft_SetStyle|Draft SetStyle]] command. For a scale of {{Value|1:100}} enter {{Value|100}}.

==Notes==

* See also: [[Draft_SetStyle|Draft SetStyle]] and [[Draft_ApplyStyle|Draft ApplyStyle]].


